<extentreports>
    <configuration>
        <theme>standard</theme>
        <encoding>utf-8</encoding>
        <protocol>https</protocol>
        <documentTitle>Automation Test Report</documentTitle>
        <reportName>Hybrid Selenium Framework Execution Report</reportName>
        <timestampFormat>MMM dd, yyyy HH:mm:ss</timestampFormat>
    </configuration>
</extentreports>

<!--
	What's happening:
<theme>standard</theme> – Standard (light) look; you could change it to dark.

<encoding>utf-8</encoding> – Character encoding.

<protocol>https</protocol> – Secure protocol, not really critical here.

<documentTitle> – Title in browser tab.

<reportName> – Main heading in the report.

<timestampFormat> – How date/time appears.

How to remember:
Just ask: “What do I want my HTML report to look like?”
Then describe it in simple tags:

theme, title, name, timestamp format.

-->
